"Abstract The road warrior has become a veritable moving office, but an office nonetheless that needs the same protection as its more traditional sibling. The same access control and authentication procedures apply. The same data has to be secured and protected. This data is routinely accessed at docking stations in hotels, trains, aeroplanes, homes offices, and quite literally, on the side of the road. While many of the bigger organizations have some pretty sophisticated security solutions in place, smaller ones may have little or no control over the way their roving employees access the company’s information infrastructure."
